"Got My Heart Set on You" is a 1986 single written by Dobie Gray and Bud Reneau and recorded by John Conlee. "Got My Heart Set on You" was John Conlee's seventh and final number one country hit. The single went to number one for one week and spent a total of fourteen weeks on the country chart.[1] John Denver recorded this song on his 1985 album Dreamland Express.
